      },
      "lineNbr": 0,
      "author": {
        "id": 6155
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-10-28T13:59:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thanks for the clarifications - is the intention with the SK_USE_DWRITE_COMPATIBLE_CONTRAST macro to use it for your testing? Or in other words, could you explain where you plan to be going with this flag?",
      "parentUuid": "b841f7f2_754e09e2",
      "revId": "4d495a0baee69df16e328d06ed6874f6e7027f67",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9c41ae60_66c0cebb",
        "filename": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 0,
      "author": {
        "id": 10586
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-10-28T18:12:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It was intended to start this conversation! 😊  To see if there is desire \u0026 willingness to adjust the contrast algorithm (at least on Windows), and prompt discussion about how to stage it, given the testing/screenshot implications.\n\nIdeally we\u0027d be able to put this behind a runtime flag so Chromium could roll it out gradually (and maybe A/B test), but I don\u0027t see an easy way to do that.  Is there a precedent for passing Chromium runtime flags into Skia, somehow?\n\n---\nFWIW, I\u0027ve been testing locally and providing custom Chromium builds for a few people internally.  I\u0027m building against *this* Skia CL, combined with a Chromium CL:  https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/2353360.\n\nThe results at this point are mostly within rounding-error territory compared with DWrite itself.  Direct screenshot comparisons against the other browsers are difficult due to layout differences (and because Spartan just hardcodes contrast\u003d1.0), but we\u0027ve been pleased with the results so far.",
      "parentUuid": "2d5ea7b6_65a3029c",
      "revId": "4d495a0baee69df16e328d06ed6874f6e7027f67",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f26ad532_e0261757",
        "filename": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 0,
      "author": {
        "id": 10586
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-10-29T23:37:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Also: Let me know if you think I should split the SK_USE_DWRITE_COMPATIBLE_CONTRAST change from the SkSurfaceProps part of the change.\n\nThey\u0027re certainly related, but independent enough that splitting the change might make sense.",
      "parentUuid": "9c41ae60_66c0cebb",
      "revId": "4d495a0baee69df16e328d06ed6874f6e7027f67",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "531dc0bf_3c984e0a",
        "filename": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 0,
      "author": {
        "id": 6155
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-10-30T17:35:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes, I am almost always in favour of more splitting. Agree that that would make sense. But also, we need to be clear, why we want the SK_USE_DWRITE_COMPATIBLE_CONTRAST define and put a justification in a comment in the code. I am not a Skia OWNER/reviewer myself, but as my 2 cents: I\u0027d be okay with having this define temporarily for your testing, but then at some point we need a setup where this is tested and not just hidden code.",
      "parentUuid": "f26ad532_e0261757",
      "revId": "4d495a0baee69df16e328d06ed6874f6e7027f67",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
