      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-11-12T03:01:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "FWIW, changes like this in Skia always need to be start life behind an #ifdef so that auto-rolling into Chromium (and Android, etc.) doesn\u0027t break things.  We\u0027d eventually turn it on by default and remove the #ifdef.\n\nAnyway... I\u0027ve removed the DWrite-compatible contrast stuff from this change, and will post a 2nd CL for continued discussion on that topic.",
      "parentUuid": "531dc0bf_3c984e0a",
      "revId": "4d495a0baee69df16e328d06ed6874f6e7027f67",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
